# Cloudflare Pages cache headers.
#
# Without these, Pages' defaults apply — and the default for .js gives
# sw.js `max-age=14400` (4 HOURS). A freshly-deployed site could then
# hand back the PREVIOUS build's service worker, whose precache
# manifest points at chunk URLs that no longer exist; those requests
# fall into the SPA catch-all and return index.html as "JavaScript",
# which is exactly the "PokerGrid just updated" reload loop. HTML and
# the worker script must always revalidate.
#
# Later rules override earlier ones for the same header, so the
# hashed, content-addressed /assets/* get the immutable long cache
# back after the catch-all.

/*
  Cache-Control: no-cache

/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/icons/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=86400
